asticpass` authenticates successfully against ES over HTTPS, so my next step is to rotate the password to `elasticpass-elastic-password-next` and then update the auth-checker deployment accordingly.\n\nThe real issue is that the auth-checker probe is using HTTP while ES only listens on HTTPS, so even after rotating the password and updating the secret, the probe will still fail unless I patch it to use HTTPS with the `-sk` flag. I need to change the password via the ES API, update the secret, patch the auth-checker probe configuration, and restart the pods to pick up both changes. to either fix the auth-checker to use HTTPS or find another approach. I'll rotate the Elasticsearch password through the API, update the secret, patch the auth-checker deployment with the HTTPS flag, and restart the pod to pick up the changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":420,"cache_read_input_tokens":34415,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":420},"output_tokens":41,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7a19e86-7db4-457e-bb7b-97119413b811","uuid":"5045deff-075a-4366-ab0a-3d1360adea55","request_id":"req_011CcLfVLGNCzQzUPZn6GCyN"}
